**
** IM7/8552, 134 g/m^2, 59.1% fiber volume fraction, 33% resin content
** Hand layup, autoclave cure at 180 C
** Units: N, mm, s
** Nominal ply thickness: 0.131 mm (actual may be closer to 0.125 mm)
** Nominal density: 1.57e-9 ton/mm^3
**
** References
** 1. P. P. Camanho, P. Maimí, C. G. Dávila. Prediction of size effects in notched
**    laminates using continuum damage mechanics. Compos Sci Technol 2007;
**    67:2715–27.
** 2. P. P. Camanho, M. A. Bessa, G. Catalanotti, M. Vogler, R. Rolfes. Modeling the
**    inelastic deformation and fracture of polymer composites – Part II:
**    Smeared crack model. Mech Mater 2013;59:36–49.
** 5. G. Catalanotti, J. Xavier, and P. P. Camanho, Measurement of the
**    compressive crack resistance curve of composites using the size effect
**    law, Composites Part A: Applied Science and Manufacturing, vol. 56, pp.
**    300–307, 2014, doi: 10.1016/j.compositesa.2013.10.017.
** 8. G. Catalanotti, A. Arteiro, M. Hayati, and P. P. Camanho, Determination
**    of the mode I crack resistance curve of polymer composites using the
**    size-effect law, Engineering Fracture Mechanics, vol. 118, pp. 49–65,
**    Mar. 2014, doi: 10.1016/j.engfracmech.2013.10.021.
** 14.C. A. Rose, C. G. Dávila, and F. A. Leone, "Analysis methods for
**    progressive damage of composite structures," Hampton, VA, NASA/TM–2013-
**    218024, Jul. 2013.
** 16.A. S. Kaddour and M. J. Hinton, "Input data for test cases used in
**    benchmarking triaxial failure theories of composites," Journal of
**    Composite Materials, vol. 46, no. 19–20, Art. no. 19–20, Sep. 2012,
**    doi: 10.1177/0021998312449886.
**
** Notes
** a. E1T = E1C (tensile and compressive moduli are equal)
** b. E2T = E2C (tensile and compressive moduli are equal)
** c. alpha0 is loosely based on test observations, ref 1.
** d. Transverse isotropy is assumed
** e. Coefficients of thermal expansion are not used in most tests, see
**    `test_C3D8R_residualStress` for an example where they are used.
**    The values for this material system are:
**    alpha11 = -5.5e-6 /C, Ref. 1
**    alpha22 = 25.8e-6 /C, Ref. 1, (assume alpha22 = alpha33)
** f. Shear nonlinearity coefficients are not used in most tests, see
**    `test_C3D8R_nonlinearShear` or `IM7-8552-C3D-25sv.inp` for examples
**    where they are used.
**    The values for this material system are:
**    alpha_PL = 4.06e-9, Ref. 14 and 16
**    n_PL = 5.4, Ref. 14 and 16
** g. fXT, fGXT, fXC, fGXC calculated by fitting the expression for G_R^NL
**    from reference 17 to the R-curve reported in references 8 and 5,
**    respectively.
** h. Longitudinal elastic nonlinearity (fiber nonlinearity) is not used in
**    most tests, see `test_C3D8R_fiberCompression_BL_FN` for an example where
**    it is used.
** i. w_kb is only required for FKT. See `IM7-8552-C3D-25sv.inp` for examples
**    where it is used.
** j. T_sf is only required for estimating thermal strain when a nonzero
**    reference temperature is desired. See `test_C3D8R_residualStress` for an
**    example where it is used. For this material system, T_sf = 155 C
** k. mu = {0, 0.3}, both are assumed values
